A ) , but it turns out that better data very much makes for better models t=
hat are cheaper to build and serve.

It=E2=80=99s also notable that Mistral is based in France; Mensch has alrea=
dy played an important role in persuading the French government to push for=
 less restrictive regulation on foundation models by the E.U.; more broadly=
, Mistral is perhaps the biggest hope for a European tech giant. Mistral is=
 doing its part: the company has released multiple models, most of them ope=
n source, which are generally thought to outperform direct competitors (pri=
marily Meta=E2=80=99s Llama), and this week the company released a large mo=
del (that it has not open-sourced) that is GPT-4 competitive.

Microsoft=E2=80=99s Investment
----------------------

Mistral=E2=80=99s large model wasn=E2=80=99t the only news it announced thi=
s week; that Wall Street Journal article included this tidbit:

The industry is taking note. Mistral has attracted interest from corporate =
clients and investors, including Microsoft, which on Monday said that it is=
 adding Mistral=E2=80=99s new model as an option for developers on its Azur=
e cloud service. As part of the multiyear deal, Microsoft will take a small=
 stake in the company.

Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-02-27/microsoft-s-=
mistral-ai-investment-to-be-examined-by-eu-watchdog ) reported more details=
:

Mistral announced a =E2=80=9Cstrategic partnership=E2=80=9D with Microsoft =
on Monday that includes making the startup=E2=80=99s latest artificial inte=
lligence models available to customers of Microsoft=E2=80=99s Azure cloud. =
Microsoft said the investment amounted to =E2=82=AC15 million ($16.3 millio=
n)=E2=80=A6Microsoft=E2=80=99s investments will convert into equity as part=
 of Mistral=E2=80=99s next funding round.

Mistral=E2=80=99s last round valued the company at $2.1 billion, which woul=
d put Microsoft=E2=80=99s share at less than 1%; however, the next round is=
 likely to be substantially more, so the actual percentage will be even les=
s. The E.U. is already threatening to investigate the investment ( https://=
www.ft.com/content/cd6eb51a-3276-450f-87fd-97e8410db9eb ) , like it is Micr=
osoft=E2=80=99s investment in OpenAI, but that seems pretty unnecessary giv=
en the size of the stake.

Still, the fact the investment exists is notable: this is a very logical re=
sponse by Microsoft to last fall=E2=80=99s upheaval at OpenAI ( https://str=
